<item>
            <title>[DERBY-4704] Incorrect nullability when casting non-nullable VARCHAR to BOOLEAN</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-4704</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With the following table definition and query&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CREATE TABLE T (X VARCHAR(10) NOT NULL);&lt;br/&gt;
INSERT INTO T VALUES &apos;true&apos;, &apos;false&apos;, &apos;unknown&apos;;&lt;br/&gt;
SELECT CAST(X AS BOOLEAN) FROM T;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the meta-data for the returned result will say that the column is not nullable, although it will contain a NULL value in the third row.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12467327">DERBY-4704</key>
